				\begin{document}$${\int }_{0}^{\infty }{\sigma }_{1}$$\end{document}(ω) dω = πne2/2me, where me is the rest mass of the electron52. For a finite-energy range, the integral can be expressed as W = ∫E1E2σ1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
